        Difference between port and target port in service:

Difference:

port → the port exposed by the Service (clients use this)
targetPort → the port on the Pod/container (where your app listens)

🔹 Example
ports:
  - port: 80
    targetPort: 8080

👉 Request flow:
Client → Service:80 → Pod:8080

🔹 Key idea

Service acts as a middle layer:
it receives traffic on port and forwards it to targetPort on Pods.











