Difference between controller and scheduler

Controller
What it does: Ensures the desired state is maintained
Watches cluster state and fixes differences
Example: If a Pod dies → controller creates a new one

👉 Think: “Keep things running as defined”

Scheduler
What it does: Decides where a Pod runs
Assigns Pods to specific nodes based on resources, rules, constraints

👉 Think: “Pick the best node”

One-line difference
Controller = maintains state
Scheduler = assigns placement

